
         Cathexis IRCd — Security-Hardened Nefarious2 IRC Daemon
         =======================================================

See README.md for the current project documentation.

Cathexis is a security-hardened fork of the Nefarious2 IRC daemon (based
on ircu/IRCu2). It retains full compatibility with the P10 server protocol
and existing Nefarious2 networks while adding modern IRCv3 capabilities,
end-to-end encryption, and comprehensive security hardening.

Version: 1.4.0
Base: Nefarious2 (u2.10.12.15)
Protocol: P10
License: GNU General Public License v2+

For build instructions, feature list, and security information, see README.md.
For the changelog, see CHANGELOG.md.
For the security audit, see AUDIT.md.
For security policy and vulnerability reporting, see SECURITY.md.
